<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="417" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d417">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/856</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">The
                                        White House, Washington</hi></placeName> [<date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-06">December 6,
                                1941</date>].</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Cordell</hi>: Shoot this<note n="69" xml:id="d417fn69">See document <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>.</note>
                            to Grew—I think it can go in gray code—saves time—I don’t mind if it
                            gets picked up.</p>
                        <closer><signed>F.D.R.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
